enzen innerhalb einer erinnerungskulturellen Gemeinschaft kommunizieren. Die versammelten exemplarischen Analysen zeigen: Literatur kann ein Ort sein, um anders über Versöhnung zu sprechen.  afunded by Fritz Thyssen Stiftung  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aDeutschland. 4aErinnerung. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aGermanistik. 4aHolocaust. 4aIdentität. 4aJudentum. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aVergangenheitsbewältigung. 4aVerzeihen. 4aWiedergutmachung. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aAmends.  aComing To Terms With the Past.  aCultural History.  aForgiveness.  aGerman Literature.  aGermany.  aHolocaust.  aIdentity.  aJudaism.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMemory Culture.  aMemory.1 aBanki, Luisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerrari, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Saskia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForkel, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForkel, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGisbertz, Anna-Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrätzel, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKodalle, Klaus-Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKörner, Birgit M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarten, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPick, Bianca Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPick, Bianca Patricia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/e